Day_6 (Daily Practice)                                                                                            (16-07-2021)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Question
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Broken Bridge
--------------
Create a function which validates whether a bridge is safe to walk on (i.e. has no gaps in it to fall through).

Examples
isSafeBridge("####") ? true

isSafeBridge("## ####") ? false

isSafeBridge("#") ? true
Notes
You can expect the bridge's ends connecting it to its surrounding.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Solution:
-------------
#include<iostream>
using namespace std;

void isSafeBridge(string a);

int main(){
    isSafeBridge("######");     	
}

void isSafeBridge(string a){
	char c=' ';
	int flag=0;
	for(int i=0;a[i]!='\0';i++){
		if(a[i]==c){
			flag=flag+1;
		}
		else{
			
		}
	}
	if(flag==0){
		cout<<"Bridge is safe\n";
	}
	else{
		cout<<"Bridge is not safe\n";
	}
}
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Learnings:
1. while using void return type function we will often use cout in it . If this is thr case the we 
   dont need to write cout<<func_name(args) in main(). We only need to write func_name(args).
2. Using void return type functions.   
